-- South African Stocks: Anglo, BHP, Aspen, Metrofile, Mr Price
-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 2012-04-20T16:01:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/south-african-stocks-anglo-bhp-aspen-metrofile-mr-price.html
The  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index (JALSH) 
advanced for a fourth day, the longest winning streak in more
than two months, gaining 0.3 percent to 34,216.55 by the close
in Johannesburg. The index climbed 1.5 percent this week.  The following are among the most active equities in the
market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Anglo American Plc (AGL)  , the diversified miner that
makes up about 9 percent of the index, climbed 0.8 percent to
295.79 rand, a fourth day of gains. Copper rose in  London ,
buoyed by shrinking inventories of the metal, signs of demand
from carmakers and an unexpected gain in German business
confidence.  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BIL)  , the world’s biggest resources
company, added 0.4 percent to 247.34 rand, a third day of gains.  Aspen Pharmacare Holdings Ltd. (APN)  , the Southern
Hemisphere’s largest drugmaker, gained the most in almost three
years, jumping 5.9 percent to 122.89 rand. Earnings will be
boosted by the purchase of drug ranges from GlaxoSmithKline Plc,
the company said today.  Metrofile Holdings Ltd. (MFL)  , a filing and document-
management company, climbed to the highest in almost three
weeks, rising 3.3 percent to 3.10 rand. Sabvest Ltd. increased
its interest in the company to 6 percent, it said today.  Mr Price Group Ltd. (MPC)  , a South African clothing and
furniture retailer, rose to a record, adding 2.1 percent to
103.48 rand. Credit Suisse Group AG raised its price estimate
for the shares to 110 rand, from 76 rand.  To contact the reporters on this story:
